crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature detects the presence of a number of Windows API functionality often seen within embedded executables. When this signature alerts on an executable, it is not an indication of malicious behavior. However, if seen firing in other file types, deeper investigation may be warranted.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: InQuest Labs

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, Go BuildID=tIsbjrlbqsgvTvT1mgs3/X5wElQ3KFR9Clx0JbJVt/D01_QCJY-Ua9o9uScw6a/lFurdYw6Pm3sr3RHZBGh, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Go-based backdoor/tunneling tool. It incorporates libraries for creating SOCKS5 proxies (`github.com/armon/go-socks5`), multiplexing network streams (`github.com/hashicorp/yamux`), and spawning interactive pseudo-terminals (`github.com/creack/pty`). This combination of functionalities enables remote command execution, interactive reverse shells, and covert network tunneling, which are characteristic behaviors of a Remote Access Trojan (RAT).
